--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
DESCRIPTION
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

This role manages passwd.

'/etc/passwd' is a text file which defines the users on the system.

For more detailed information on the usage and available configuration options
please consult the following sections.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
USAGE
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

INSTALL
  - hosts: all
    roles:
      - role: passwd
    vars:
      passwd_state: 'install'

DISABLE
  - hosts: all
    roles:
      - role: passwd
    vars:
      passwd_state: 'disable'

INACTIVE
  - hosts: all
    roles:
      - role: passwd
    vars:
      passwd_state: 'inactive'

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
VARIABLES
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

ROLE
  passwd_state
    Description: Control the state of the role.
                 'passwd' is a core file and can therefore not be removed.
    Implemented: 0.1
    Required   : False
    Value      : Predetermined
    Type       : String
    Default    : 'install'
    Options    :
      Install : 'true' | 'yes' | 'install'
      Disable : 'false' | 'no' | 'disable'
      Inactive: 'quiesce' | 'inactive'

